quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  38,65,"Say: \"I am but a warner. There is no deity save God, the One (with no-one and nothing like or comparable to Him), the All-Overwhelming (with absolute sway over all that exists)"
  38,66,"The Lord of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them, the All-Glorious with irresistible might, the All-Forgiving"
  38,67,"Say: \"This (Qur’an) is a supreme message"
  38,68,You turn away from it in aversion
  38,69,I had no knowledge of the High Assembly (in the heavens) when they were arguing
  38,70,I (follow only what is revealed to me and) it is revealed to me that I am but a plain warner
  38,71,"(Remember) when your Lord said to the angels: \"I am creating a mortal out of clay (to set him on the earth as vicegerent)"
  38,72,"When I have fashioned him fully and breathed into Him out of My Spirit, then fall down prostrating before him (as a sign of respect for him and his superiority)"
  38,73,"So the angels prostrated, all of them together"
  38,74,But Iblis did not (in defiance of God’s explicit order to him); he grew arrogant and displayed himself as an unbeliever
  38,75,"(God) said: \"O Iblis! What prevents you from prostrating before the being whom I have created with My two Hands? Are you too proud (to bow down before any created being in defiance of My command), or are you (of those who think themselves) so high in honor (that they cannot be ordered to prostrate before anyone)"
  38,76,"(Iblis) answered: \"I am better than him. You have created me from fire and him You have created from clay"
  38,77,"(God) said: \"Then get you down out of it; surely You are one eternally rejected (from My Mercy)"
  38,78,And My curse is on you until the Day of Judgment
  38,79,"He said: \"My Lord, grant me respite till the Day when they are raised (from the dead)"
  38,80,"(God) said: \"You are of the ones granted respite"
  38,81,Until the Day of the Time Appointed
  38,82,"(Iblis) said: \"Then (I swear) by Your Glory, I will certainly cause them all to rebel and go astray"
  38,83,"Except Your servants among them, endowed with sincerity in faith and worshipping You"
  38,84,"(God) said: \"(Whatever I do and command is) the truth itself, and the truth I speak"
  38,85,"I will most certainly fill Hell with you (and your kind), and those (of humankind) who follow you, all together"
  38,86,"Say (O Messenger): \"I ask of you no wage for this (conveying the Qur’an to you), and I am not of those who claim to be what they are really not and make fabrications of their own"
  38,87,This (Qur’an) is only a Reminder (with guidance and admonishment) for all conscious beings
  38,88,You will most certainly come to know what it informs of after a time (as appointed for you)